{{Year dab|237}}
{{unreferenced|date=January 2017}}
{{Year nav|237}}
{{M1 year in topic}}
Year '''237''' ('''[[Roman numerals|CCXXXVII]]''') was a [[common year starting on Sunday]] (link will display the full calendar) of the [[Julian calendar]]. At the time, it was known as the '''Year of the Consulship of Perpetuus and Felix''' (or, less frequently, '''year 990 ''[[Ab urbe condita]]'''''). The denomination 237 for this year has been used since the early medieval period, when the [[Anno Domini]] [[calendar era]] became the prevalent method in Europe for naming years.

== Events ==
&lt;onlyinclude&gt;

=== By place ===

==== Roman Empire ====
* Emperor [[Maximinus Thrax]] campaigns on the rivers [[Danube]] and [[Rhine]] in [[Germania]], defeating the [[Alemanni]], and never visits [[Ancient Rome|Rome]]. He is accepted by the [[Roman Senate]], but taxes the rich [[aristocracy]] heavily, and engenders such hostility among them, that they [[conspiracy (political)|plot]] against him.

==== Persia ====
* King [[Ardashir I of Persia]] renews his attacks on the Roman province of [[Mesopotamia]].

=== By topic ===

==== Religion ====
* Patriarch Eugenius I succeeds [[Patriarch Castinus]] as [[Ecumenical Patriarch of Constantinople|Patriarch of Constantinople]].
* [[Saint Babylas]] becomes [[Patriarch of Antioch]].
&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;

== Births ==
* [[Alexander of Constantinople]], future Patriarch of [[Constantinople]]
* [[Philippus II]], [[Roman Emperor]] (d. [[249]])

== Deaths ==
* [[February 7]] &amp;ndash; [[Chen Qun]], Chinese minister of [[Cao Wei]]
* [[September 22]] &amp;ndash; [[Empress Mao (Ming)|Empress Mao]], Chinese empress of the Cao Wei state
* [[Wu Yi (Three Kingdoms)|Wu Yi]], Chinese general of the Shu Han state
* [[Empress Zhang (Liu Shan's first wife)|Empress Zhang]], Chinese empress of the [[Shu Han]]

